&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Tokyo Police Club - Nature of the Experiment&lt;br /&gt;
	Before Tokyo Police Club, the only other sonically-similar band I heard was Snowden. TPC has an energy and pace in songs that&amp;#39;s unmatched and keeps everything upbeat and moving. If your songs move fast, people dancing to it at your show will dance fast too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;iframe allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/embed/DPY5vTbLhs8&quot; width=&quot;420&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Bombay Bicycle Club - Ghost&lt;br /&gt;
	This song helped me understand the effect that space can have on a composition... the answer isn&amp;#39;t always adding another part. Sometime&amp;#39;s it&amp;#39;s letting all but one instrument drop out. Sometimes it&amp;#39;s a full-stop at the end of a phrase. Also, the driving bass in the mix further drives home the point that a good bass presence makes a song better.&lt;/p&gt;
